# Clothing Marketplace SaaS — Project Rules

## What this project is

A multi-tenant SaaS platform for Moroccan clothing merchants. Merchants sign up, create a store, and get a public-facing storefront at `store.platform.ma`. Customers buy via cash-on-delivery (COD) — no payment gateway. The platform charges merchants a monthly subscription (99–499 MAD).

**Business context:**
- Morocco-only market, COD-first (no Stripe, no CMI yet)
- WhatsApp is the primary notification channel (bigger than email in Morocco)
- Customers never create accounts — guest checkout only (name + phone + wilaya)
- Solo developer building this — every decision optimizes for shipping speed

---

## Tech stack

| Layer | Choice | Why |
|---|---|---|
| Framework | Next.js 15 (App Router) | SSR storefronts for SEO, API Routes + Server Actions for backend |
| Language | TypeScript strict mode | End-to-end type safety |
| Database | Supabase (PostgreSQL) | DB + Auth + Storage + Realtime in one, free tier |
| Auth | Supabase Auth | Multi-tenant JWT + RLS, zero config |
| Cache / rate limit | Upstash Redis | Serverless-friendly, free tier |
| Notifications | WhatsApp Business Cloud API | Free 1K msgs/month, dominant channel in Morocco |
| Deploy | Vercel Pro | Serverless, wildcard subdomain support, $20/mo |
| Styling | Tailwind CSS v4 | PostCSS plugin, no config file needed |
| Validation | Zod | All API inputs validated before touching DB |
| Package manager | Bun | Faster installs, same Node.js runtime on Vercel |

**Critical: this is NOT microservices.** Everything lives in one Next.js monorepo. No separate backend service. No Docker. Extract only if real bottlenecks appear at 500+ merchants.

