## Next.js 15 breaking changes — always follow these

### 1. `cookies()` is async
```ts
// ✓ correct — server.ts already handles this
const supabase = await createClient()

// ✗ wrong — will throw in Next.js 15
const supabase = createClient()
```

### 2. Route params are a Promise
```ts
// ✓ correct
export async function GET(
  request: NextRequest,
  { params }: { params: Promise<{ id: string }> }
) {
  const { id } = await params
}

// ✗ wrong — params is no longer sync in Next.js 15
export async function GET(
  request: NextRequest,
  { params }: { params: { id: string } }
) {
  const { id } = params // breaks
}
```

### 3. React 19 — `useActionState` not `useFormState`
```ts
// ✓ correct
import { useActionState } from "react"
const [state, action] = useActionState(myAction, null)

// ✗ wrong — removed in React 19
import { useFormState } from "react-dom"
```

### 4. ESM project — all config files use `export default`
The project has `"type": "module"` in package.json. Config files must use ESM syntax.

