## Database schema overview

```
auth.users (Supabase managed)
  └── profiles                  ← merchant info, auto-created by DB trigger
      └── subscriptions         ← plan + billing status
          └── stores            ← 1 on Starter/Growth, up to 3 on Pro
              ├── products
              │   ├── attribute_definitions   ← "Taille", "Couleur", "Matière"
              │   │   └── attribute_values    ← "M", "Rouge", "Coton"
              │   └── product_variants        ← each size×color combo
              │       └── variant_attribute_values
              ├── orders (guest checkout — no customer account)
              │   └── order_items             ← SNAPSHOT pattern
              ├── shipping_zones              ← price per wilaya
              └── analytics_events            ← append-only event log
```

**Key design decisions:**
- Prices stored as **integers in MAD** (150 = 150 MAD). No decimals, no centimes.
- `order_items` stores **snapshots** of product name/price/image at order time. Never join to live products for past orders.
- `analytics_events` is **append-only**. Never UPDATE or DELETE rows.
- Variants use an **EAV pattern** (`attribute_definitions` → `attribute_values` → `variant_attribute_values`) to support any attribute type (size, color, material, condition for vintage, etc.) without schema changes.

